<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='255000' id='t-255000'>of the hospital where I was working.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='257000' id='t-257000'>At the time I was assigned
to the cardiology service</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='259500' id='t-259500'>on a cardiology rotation.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='261000' id='t-261000'>And it was my job,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='263000' id='t-263000'>when the emergency staff called
for a cardiology consult,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='265739' id='t-265739'>to see that patient in emerg.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='268000' id='t-268000'>and to report back to my attending.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='270000' id='t-270000'>And I saw Mrs. Drucker,
and she was breathless.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='273000' id='t-273000'>And when I listened to her,
